1
00:00:11,116 --> 00:00:13,160
[rock music playing]

2
00:00:43,148 --> 00:00:46,402
CHAPTER 42:
WHY ONLY HER?

3
00:00:46,485 --> 00:00:47,570
[confrontational music plays]

4
00:00:47,653 --> 00:00:50,072
[Ha-su] What if
Mr. Ga finds out what you're doing?

5
00:00:50,781 --> 00:00:54,118
Will you still be able to talk to him
like that once he knows the truth?

6
00:00:54,869 --> 00:00:56,370
[Woo-su] Here. Cheer up.

7
00:00:59,081 --> 00:01:00,791
[Ha-su] Wait and see, Yeo Eui-ju.

8
00:01:01,458 --> 00:01:02,668
You're done for.

9
00:01:06,922 --> 00:01:08,173
COUNSELING IN PROGRESS

10
00:01:09,758 --> 00:01:11,302
[music ends]

11
00:01:12,261 --> 00:01:13,846
Tell me. What is it?

12
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:16,599
I was torn whether to tell you.

13
00:01:17,349 --> 00:01:19,143
But I think you should know who it is.

14
00:01:20,853 --> 00:01:22,563
Someone in our class

15
00:01:23,147 --> 00:01:25,065
is writing a web novel about you.

16
00:01:26,066 --> 00:01:28,152
A BL novel at that.

17
00:01:29,069 --> 00:01:30,779
It's already all over the Internet.

18
00:01:32,781 --> 00:01:34,366
And guess who that is.

19
00:01:37,536 --> 00:01:38,787
It's Yeo Eui-ju.

20
00:01:39,622 --> 00:01:41,624
[tense music plays]

21
00:01:44,293 --> 00:01:45,961
I said it's Yeo Eui-ju.

22
00:01:48,380 --> 00:01:49,882
[sighs]

23
00:01:49,965 --> 00:01:51,258
I know.

24
00:01:53,802 --> 00:01:55,304
You know about it?

25
00:01:56,305 --> 00:01:57,389
But how?

26
00:01:59,016 --> 00:02:01,810
Mr. Ga, are you seriously okay with it?
Aren't you offended?

27
00:02:02,603 --> 00:02:05,689
That girl, Yeo Eui-ju,
is so creepy and scary.

28
00:02:06,649 --> 00:02:08,734
You really need to read
that novel yourself.

29
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,201
Don't tell me.

30
00:02:18,243 --> 00:02:19,495
You already read it too?

31
00:02:23,999 --> 00:02:26,126
And you chose to do nothing about her?

32
00:02:27,252 --> 00:02:28,629
Why, Mr. Ga?

33
00:02:29,630 --> 00:02:31,423
Why do you play favorites with her?

34
00:02:33,342 --> 00:02:34,343
What are you talking about?

35
00:02:34,426 --> 00:02:37,137
Why is it that
the only one you care about is her?

36
00:02:39,306 --> 00:02:41,892
I mean, why bother with a girl like that?

37
00:02:41,976 --> 00:02:43,852
The after-school class and her novel…

38
00:02:43,936 --> 00:02:44,937
Why the special treatment?

39
00:02:46,981 --> 00:02:48,190
Someone like her

40
00:02:48,774 --> 00:02:51,151
doesn't need to be
someone you worry about.

41
00:02:52,486 --> 00:02:54,780
I think you're sorely mistaken.

42
00:02:55,614 --> 00:02:57,408
She's not an exception.

43
00:02:58,742 --> 00:03:00,327
I would've done the same, even for you.

44
00:03:01,078 --> 00:03:03,163
What you're saying is just a cliché.

45
00:03:03,914 --> 00:03:04,915
My point is,

46
00:03:04,999 --> 00:03:08,293
shouldn't you be focusing more on me
than on someone like Yeo Eui-ju?

47
00:03:09,086 --> 00:03:10,546
I'm Eun Ha-su.

48
00:03:10,629 --> 00:03:12,006
I'm the Eun Ha-su!

49
00:03:12,506 --> 00:03:14,717
[breathing shakily]

50
00:03:24,852 --> 00:03:26,854
[sad music playing]

51
00:03:35,112 --> 00:03:36,864
I'll ruin you both.

52
00:03:42,786 --> 00:03:45,080
CHAPTER 43:
WHO IS IMUK?

53
00:03:45,164 --> 00:03:46,165
[phone buzzes]

54
00:03:50,502 --> 00:03:51,754
[phone buzzing]

55
00:03:51,837 --> 00:03:54,673
CHECK THIS OUT
THIS IS ABOUT OUR TEACHERS?

56
00:03:54,757 --> 00:03:56,467
[buzzing continues]

57
00:03:56,550 --> 00:03:58,385
[tense music playing]

58
00:04:00,012 --> 00:04:02,139
[students chattering]

59
00:04:07,269 --> 00:04:08,854
[Ha-su] Girls, check out this novel.

60
00:04:08,937 --> 00:04:10,606
I hear it's about our teachers,

61
00:04:10,689 --> 00:04:12,441
and the writer goes to our school.

62
00:04:17,321 --> 00:04:18,906
[tense music continues]

63
00:04:18,989 --> 00:04:20,532
-Did you see this?
-[clamoring]

64
00:04:22,868 --> 00:04:25,412
I had no idea. What do we do?

65
00:04:25,954 --> 00:04:27,206
WE WERE FRIENDS

66
00:04:27,289 --> 00:04:29,500
-[students shrieking]
-Did you see this? Is it true?

67
00:04:29,583 --> 00:04:31,877
That was so insane.

68
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:34,421
-Oh, my God.
-This is insane.

69
00:04:34,505 --> 00:04:36,465
-Come on. Now read it.
-[students clamoring]

70
00:04:42,638 --> 00:04:44,056
[music fades]

71
00:04:44,139 --> 00:04:45,390
[grunts]

72
00:04:45,474 --> 00:04:46,600
The letters are way too small.

73
00:04:46,683 --> 00:04:47,684
EPISODE 14

74
00:04:47,768 --> 00:04:49,228
So what did you say this was?

75
00:04:49,853 --> 00:04:50,896
It's a gay romance.

76
00:04:50,979 --> 00:04:52,815
The genre is called BL.

77
00:04:52,898 --> 00:04:55,150
And the main characters are based on
our school's new teachers.

78
00:04:55,234 --> 00:04:58,570
They have romantic feelings
for each other in the novel.

79
00:04:58,654 --> 00:05:00,572
In the story, Mr. Ga and Mr. Jung

80
00:05:00,656 --> 00:05:03,408
-are in a love triangle over Mr. Yoon.
-[exclaims]

81
00:05:03,492 --> 00:05:06,328
Stop, stop. Please, this is enough. Stop.

82
00:05:06,411 --> 00:05:08,789
[sighs] I can't believe what I just heard.

83
00:05:08,872 --> 00:05:09,873
Oh, I feel dizzy. Ugh…

84
00:05:09,957 --> 00:05:11,083
This is clearly defamation

85
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:13,293
and a violation of our teacher's rights.

86
00:05:14,294 --> 00:05:17,840
If it's shared online where everyone can
see it, reporters will wirite about it.

87
00:05:17,923 --> 00:05:18,966
[mischievous music playing]

88
00:05:19,049 --> 00:05:20,342
But, of course…

89
00:05:20,425 --> 00:05:21,802
That can't happen.

90
00:05:21,885 --> 00:05:23,554
I can't stand the thought of my own school

91
00:05:23,637 --> 00:05:26,807
being dragged through that kind of
disgusting and disturbing gossip.

92
00:05:26,890 --> 00:05:27,933
[chuckles]

93
00:05:28,016 --> 00:05:29,893
Yes, of course. You're right.

94
00:05:29,977 --> 00:05:31,812
These matters must be handled
within the school

95
00:05:31,895 --> 00:05:33,397
as quietly as possible.

96
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,065
Oh, my head.

97
00:05:35,149 --> 00:05:37,192
Not a single peaceful day
in this darn school

98
00:05:37,276 --> 00:05:39,778
[sighing loudly]

99
00:05:39,862 --> 00:05:43,615
I'll make sure to take care of this.
Don't worry. You can go back to class.

100
00:05:43,699 --> 00:05:45,909
[mischievous music continues]

101
00:05:51,123 --> 00:05:52,249
[grunts]

102
00:05:53,292 --> 00:05:54,501
[music ends]

103
00:06:02,759 --> 00:06:04,344
Huh? [grunts]

104
00:06:15,272 --> 00:06:16,481
It's you, isn't it?

105
00:06:17,399 --> 00:06:19,401
Is it you?
Did you really write that novel?

106
00:06:19,985 --> 00:06:21,737
With our teachers as its main characters?

107
00:06:24,448 --> 00:06:25,699
Yeah.

108
00:06:27,201 --> 00:06:28,452
This is nuts.

109
00:06:30,996 --> 00:06:32,289
Go-ya, what happened is--

110
00:06:32,372 --> 00:06:34,166
So that's the reason why
you looked so out of it?

111
00:06:35,417 --> 00:06:38,795
You should've told me, at least.
You must've been so lonely on your own.

112
00:06:42,174 --> 00:06:44,176
[tender music playing]

113
00:06:45,636 --> 00:06:47,971
Did you think I wouldn't understand you
if you told me?

114
00:06:49,056 --> 00:06:50,599
No, Go-ya.

115
00:06:50,682 --> 00:06:52,309
Tha'ts not it.

116
00:06:52,392 --> 00:06:54,519
It's not that I couldn't trust you.

117
00:06:54,603 --> 00:06:55,604
I just…

118
00:06:56,647 --> 00:06:57,648
[sighs]

119
00:06:58,899 --> 00:07:00,567
I think I was embarrassed.

120
00:07:03,987 --> 00:07:05,656
I was ashamed of myself.

121
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:10,619
I saw your novel got so many views.

122
00:07:11,203 --> 00:07:13,872
You promised you'd tell me first
if your piece became a hit.

123
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:17,709
I'm sorry.

124
00:07:20,921 --> 00:07:22,422
How did you get caught?

125
00:07:23,131 --> 00:07:25,008
How did Eun Ha-su find out about it?

126
00:07:26,593 --> 00:07:29,471
[sighs] I really have no idea.

127
00:07:30,138 --> 00:07:32,099
All I know is that she caught on

128
00:07:32,182 --> 00:07:33,517
a few days ago.

129
00:07:35,936 --> 00:07:38,814
You silly girl.
Writing about our teachers?

130
00:07:39,398 --> 00:07:41,066
You're seriously insane.

131
00:07:41,149 --> 00:07:42,943
It's all right. I forgive you

132
00:07:43,735 --> 00:07:44,820
Let's go.

133
00:07:45,404 --> 00:07:46,405
Come on.

134
00:07:48,907 --> 00:07:49,908
[music ends]

135
00:07:49,992 --> 00:07:51,493
"If you don't wanna solve problems,

136
00:07:51,576 --> 00:07:52,911
you can do something else with me."

137
00:07:52,995 --> 00:07:54,538
-[laughs]
-Oh, please!

138
00:07:56,290 --> 00:07:59,376
-What now?
-Geez.

139
00:08:03,797 --> 00:08:05,090
-Hey.
-Eun Ha-su.

140
00:08:05,173 --> 00:08:07,301
[Dan-ji] How can you be so sure
that Eui-ju is Imuk?

141
00:08:07,384 --> 00:08:08,552
Huh? Where's the evidence?

142
00:08:08,635 --> 00:08:11,430
Mr. Ga is quoted in the novel
word-for-word.

143
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:14,349
You can tell for yourselves.

144
00:08:14,433 --> 00:08:17,144
What he said during
the first day of school is in there too.

145
00:08:18,312 --> 00:08:20,897
Look, to be honest,
it's not much of a crime. Okay?

146
00:08:20,981 --> 00:08:22,149
What's wrong with that?

147
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:24,443
Don't you think

148
00:08:25,068 --> 00:08:26,653
people like her are weird?

149
00:08:26,737 --> 00:08:28,363
Ugh. So creepy.

150
00:08:28,447 --> 00:08:31,033
[scoffs] Hey, to each their own.

151
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:33,785
Whatever others like
is none of your business.

152
00:08:33,869 --> 00:08:37,789
Even so, she shouldn't have written
such a story about our teachers.

153
00:08:37,873 --> 00:08:41,376
Imagine someone pairing us up and writing
a messed-up story behind our backs.

154
00:08:41,460 --> 00:08:45,130
Maybe she's already writing a lesbian
story about our school or something.

155
00:08:45,213 --> 00:08:46,715
-[sighs]
-That's freaking creepy

156
00:08:46,798 --> 00:08:49,217
People like that,
use freedom of expression

157
00:08:49,301 --> 00:08:51,386
as an excuse and end up as criminals.

158
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:52,471
Hey…

159
00:08:56,099 --> 00:08:57,934
-[stammers]
-We can ask her directly.

160
00:08:59,936 --> 00:09:02,689
-Hi, Eui-ju.
-Hi, Eui-ju. Good morning

161
00:09:03,940 --> 00:09:05,192
Good morning.

162
00:09:08,862 --> 00:09:12,699
If this goes to a disciplinary committee,
her parents will be told about it

163
00:09:12,783 --> 00:09:15,410
My parents reading my BL novel?

164
00:09:15,494 --> 00:09:17,371
I'd be gone before they do.

165
00:09:17,454 --> 00:09:19,039
-That's true.
-[student 1] So true.

166
00:09:19,122 --> 00:09:20,999
Actually, I'd wanna just vanish
into thin air.

167
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:23,418
-[student 2] Agreed.
-[student 3] It sure is messed up.

168
00:09:23,502 --> 00:09:25,045
Damn it, you crazy bitch!

169
00:09:25,128 --> 00:09:26,129
[screams]

170
00:09:26,213 --> 00:09:28,840
[students clamoring, screaming]

171
00:09:35,263 --> 00:09:37,474
This is enough!

172
00:09:38,141 --> 00:09:39,309
What's going on?

173
00:09:39,393 --> 00:09:40,394
[clamoring stops]

174
00:09:44,022 --> 00:09:45,023
[student grunts]

175
00:10:08,296 --> 00:10:09,297
[Woo-su] Yeo Eui-ju,

176
00:10:10,298 --> 00:10:11,550
follow me.

177
00:10:20,559 --> 00:10:22,102
[clamoring resumes]

178
00:10:22,185 --> 00:10:24,104
What the hell is wrong with you?

179
00:10:24,187 --> 00:10:25,689
Hang on. Hey stop.

180
00:10:25,772 --> 00:10:26,982
What's wrong with you?

181
00:10:27,566 --> 00:10:32,237
CHAPTER 44: YOU MUST TAKE
RESPONSIBILITY FOR YOUR ACTIONS

182
00:10:49,171 --> 00:10:50,172
Mr. Ga.

183
00:10:52,299 --> 00:10:54,509
Just act like you didn't know. Okay?

184
00:10:57,304 --> 00:11:00,056
I don't want you getting in trouble at all
because of me.

185
00:11:03,643 --> 00:11:06,354
Since when does a cornered rat
worry about the cat?

186
00:11:07,063 --> 00:11:09,900
It's only right
that I take responsibility for this.

187
00:11:11,151 --> 00:11:12,694
Just say that…

188
00:11:12,777 --> 00:11:13,778
that…

189
00:11:14,613 --> 00:11:15,822
that you didn't know.

190
00:11:17,407 --> 00:11:18,658
Please, sir.

191
00:11:18,742 --> 00:11:20,202
Act as if you didn't know.

192
00:11:20,285 --> 00:11:23,288
Just like the other teachers,
you didn't know anything from the start.

193
00:11:24,122 --> 00:11:26,875
I did all of this on my own.

194
00:11:28,043 --> 00:11:29,044
And, of course,

195
00:11:30,170 --> 00:11:33,256
you have nothing to do with it.

196
00:11:38,637 --> 00:11:40,805
It'll go to a disciplinary committee.

197
00:11:41,723 --> 00:11:45,101
Which in fact is inevitable but be
prepared as to what you're going to say.

198
00:11:46,061 --> 00:11:47,145
And how you say it.

199
00:11:50,357 --> 00:11:51,525
Yes, sir.

200
00:11:53,527 --> 00:11:54,986
I'm responsible as well.

201
00:11:56,321 --> 00:11:58,740
I'm partly responsible for this.
That's for sure.

202
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:02,953
But you must take responsibility for
your own actions. You can't avoid that.

203
00:12:06,081 --> 00:12:08,124
Yes. I know.

204
00:12:09,668 --> 00:12:10,877
I know you're scared.

205
00:12:11,836 --> 00:12:14,005
You must have regrets
and feel embarrassed.

206
00:12:14,089 --> 00:12:15,882
As if your world is falling apart.

207
00:12:17,008 --> 00:12:19,761
But this whole thing
is not going to end your life.

208
00:12:20,512 --> 00:12:22,639
You may be feeling like it will.

209
00:12:23,473 --> 00:12:24,808
But it won't.

210
00:12:26,101 --> 00:12:28,019
[gentle music plays]

211
00:12:28,103 --> 00:12:29,312
[sighs]

212
00:12:30,105 --> 00:12:31,940
I don't know how this will all turn out.

213
00:12:32,649 --> 00:12:34,442
But what matters here most is

214
00:12:34,526 --> 00:12:37,487
how you go through this,
how you face it and how you handle it.

215
00:12:38,196 --> 00:12:39,447
That's what matters now.

216
00:12:40,657 --> 00:12:42,075
Do you understand that?

217
00:12:44,578 --> 00:12:45,620
Yes.

218
00:12:51,501 --> 00:12:53,545
The principal wants to see you. Let's go.

219
00:12:59,509 --> 00:13:01,177
[Young-hee] What is this?

220
00:13:01,261 --> 00:13:03,638
Explain what in the world this is.
How could…

221
00:13:05,181 --> 00:13:07,601
You turned your teachers into
fictional characters.

222
00:13:07,684 --> 00:13:09,269
How can a student do this?

223
00:13:09,853 --> 00:13:12,188
This is totally ridiculous.

224
00:13:12,689 --> 00:13:14,482
Ms. Kim, let me…

225
00:13:15,483 --> 00:13:16,693
What does she take us for?

226
00:13:16,776 --> 00:13:19,404
How could a simple student
like her ridicule

227
00:13:19,487 --> 00:13:21,156
and make a fool out of her own teachers?

228
00:13:21,239 --> 00:13:23,908
Is that what you call education?
It's embarrassing!

229
00:13:23,992 --> 00:13:25,035
[breathes heavily]

230
00:13:25,118 --> 00:13:27,621
I mean, what on earth are kids learning?

231
00:13:27,704 --> 00:13:31,291
They're treating their teachers like toys!
[breathing deeply]

232
00:13:31,374 --> 00:13:32,917
[screams] Delete it immediately!

233
00:13:33,001 --> 00:13:34,669
Delete it from the Internet.

234
00:13:34,753 --> 00:13:37,088
Think about our reputation.
If the parents find out…

235
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:41,551
It's an absolute humiliation
to our school!

236
00:13:42,260 --> 00:13:43,637
I'm really sorry.

237
00:13:44,763 --> 00:13:47,557
Ms. Kim, I have something to tell you,
the truth is--

238
00:13:47,641 --> 00:13:50,143
Save that thought
for the disciplinary committee.

239
00:13:50,226 --> 00:13:52,020
And tell her parents to come over.

240
00:13:52,103 --> 00:13:53,647
Tell the other teachers too.

241
00:13:53,730 --> 00:13:55,899
Even [shudders] the ones from your novel.

242
00:13:55,982 --> 00:13:58,693
Yoon Dong-ju, Jung Gi-jeon
and Noh Da-ju as well.

243
00:13:59,361 --> 00:14:01,154
[tense music playing]

244
00:14:03,782 --> 00:14:04,908
Ma'am.

245
00:14:06,785 --> 00:14:08,203
You'll be expelled.

246
00:14:08,286 --> 00:14:10,664
I will never let this slide!

247
00:14:16,586 --> 00:14:18,213
MALE TEACHERS' LOUNGE

248
00:14:26,513 --> 00:14:27,889
-[sighs]
-Damn.

249
00:14:31,935 --> 00:14:33,186
What is this?

250
00:14:33,812 --> 00:14:34,854
[sighs]

251
00:14:35,939 --> 00:14:38,650
I admire your poor reading comprehension.

252
00:14:39,359 --> 00:14:40,360
What?

253
00:14:40,443 --> 00:14:42,362
All right, listen. So you…

254
00:14:44,197 --> 00:14:45,490
him, and Woo-su,

255
00:14:46,157 --> 00:14:47,826
you guys are all, you know,

256
00:14:48,368 --> 00:14:50,578
involved with each other. Yep.

257
00:14:50,662 --> 00:14:52,414
It's a work of pure delusion,

258
00:14:52,497 --> 00:14:55,500
fueled by some incredibly reckless
and crazy fantasies.

259
00:14:55,583 --> 00:14:57,252
What about him and me?

260
00:14:57,335 --> 00:14:59,754
[curious music playing]

261
00:15:01,047 --> 00:15:03,758
Never mind. Just forget it.

262
00:15:03,842 --> 00:15:04,843
I mean…

263
00:15:05,969 --> 00:15:07,429
[Da-ju] Ugh, that little brat!

264
00:15:07,512 --> 00:15:10,014
There was a crazy look in her eyes.
I told you.

265
00:15:10,098 --> 00:15:11,850
I'm a great judge of character.

266
00:15:14,936 --> 00:15:17,439
Hey, are you still reading that drivel?

267
00:15:17,522 --> 00:15:19,441
It's been minutes now. So tell me.

268
00:15:19,524 --> 00:15:22,986
is it a freedom of expression
or an invasion of privacy?

269
00:15:23,069 --> 00:15:25,029
-Mmm. [sniffs]
-Should we go to court?

270
00:15:25,113 --> 00:15:26,906
Is it worth filing a lawsuit or something?

271
00:15:27,532 --> 00:15:28,825
Should I hire an attorney?

272
00:15:28,908 --> 00:15:31,244
I mean, for what charges?

273
00:15:31,327 --> 00:15:32,704
Defamation.

274
00:15:32,787 --> 00:15:34,664
Calm down. Kids can play pranks like this.

275
00:15:34,748 --> 00:15:35,832
Hey, that's dangerous.

276
00:15:35,915 --> 00:15:37,876
-It's dangerous, you know.
-[music ends]

277
00:15:37,959 --> 00:15:39,753
This isn't something that
can be dismissed lightly.

278
00:15:39,836 --> 00:15:41,880
-Mm-hmm!
-No?

279
00:15:41,963 --> 00:15:45,008
Parts of the novel were written
word-for-word without permission

280
00:15:45,091 --> 00:15:47,010
I mean, our words and our actions.

281
00:15:47,635 --> 00:15:49,471
Since she didn't get our consent,

282
00:15:49,554 --> 00:15:51,723
we may file a civil lawsuit against her

283
00:15:51,806 --> 00:15:53,141
if it has caused us any harm.

284
00:15:53,224 --> 00:15:54,309
Mm.

285
00:15:55,018 --> 00:15:58,772
There's no clear boundary for
how much reality should be in fiction.

286
00:15:59,397 --> 00:16:01,441
But it may become an issue
in terms of ethics.

287
00:16:01,524 --> 00:16:02,984
[Da-ju applauding] Hell, yeah.

288
00:16:03,818 --> 00:16:06,404
That's right.
What's the occasion, Dong-ju?

289
00:16:06,488 --> 00:16:07,989
You're acting like a hard peach.

290
00:16:08,072 --> 00:16:12,243
not a mushy peach for once.
You sound tough as nails, not soft at all.

291
00:16:12,744 --> 00:16:13,828
However,

292
00:16:15,330 --> 00:16:17,582
it won't be much of an issue

293
00:16:17,665 --> 00:16:19,167
if we haven't been harmed.

294
00:16:20,001 --> 00:16:21,586
So, the punishment for Eui-ju

295
00:16:22,504 --> 00:16:24,422
depends on what we all decide.

296
00:16:24,506 --> 00:16:25,507
Mm.

297
00:16:26,883 --> 00:16:28,510
[sighs] Geez.

298
00:16:33,306 --> 00:16:34,557
What did the principal say?

299
00:16:35,183 --> 00:16:36,434
It's a mess, isn't it?

300
00:16:36,518 --> 00:16:38,895
[sighs] There'll be a committee.

301
00:16:40,063 --> 00:16:41,231
You'll have to go too.

302
00:16:43,441 --> 00:16:47,195
According to the Korean education major
and published author, Mr. Yoon Dong-ju,

303
00:16:47,278 --> 00:16:49,155
the punishment for Yeo Eui-ju,

304
00:16:49,239 --> 00:16:51,908
will differ depending on
how we decide to react.

305
00:16:51,991 --> 00:16:52,992
So what will you do?

306
00:16:56,371 --> 00:16:58,248
How should we punish her?

307
00:17:00,124 --> 00:17:01,125
Hey, Woo-su.

308
00:17:01,209 --> 00:17:04,671
Can you use that smart brain of yours
to come up with some cruel punishment.

309
00:17:04,754 --> 00:17:06,673
-Hey.
-What?

310
00:17:09,759 --> 00:17:11,261
It's up to each person.

311
00:17:12,846 --> 00:17:13,972
[Dong-ju sighs]

312
00:17:15,139 --> 00:17:17,267
[sad music plays]

313
00:17:23,147 --> 00:17:24,232
Are you okay?

314
00:17:28,611 --> 00:17:30,113
Don't mind the girls.

315
00:17:30,613 --> 00:17:32,407
They'll forget it all in a week anyway.

316
00:17:53,303 --> 00:17:54,304
[sniffles]

317
00:17:56,598 --> 00:17:58,224
[music ends]

318
00:18:01,644 --> 00:18:02,770
[sighs deeply]

319
00:18:03,521 --> 00:18:05,481
[gasps] Oh, Dad.

320
00:18:05,565 --> 00:18:08,318
Hi, Eui-ju. I didn't expect to see you.

321
00:18:09,193 --> 00:18:10,486
I can carry it.

322
00:18:11,321 --> 00:18:13,740
Why do you look so sad? Are you okay?

323
00:18:14,449 --> 00:18:15,992
No, it's just, you know…

324
00:18:16,659 --> 00:18:17,994
I'm just a little tired.

325
00:18:18,995 --> 00:18:21,831
How about you though?
You've worked overtime a lot lately.

326
00:18:21,915 --> 00:18:22,916
You're right.

327
00:18:22,999 --> 00:18:24,792
Well, I've got budgets to plan

328
00:18:25,460 --> 00:18:27,420
and complaints from residents to handle.

329
00:18:27,503 --> 00:18:28,588
Argh.

330
00:18:28,671 --> 00:18:29,756
[exhales]

331
00:18:29,839 --> 00:18:32,884
Still, all my fatigue goes away

332
00:18:32,967 --> 00:18:35,303
at the sight of my beautiful daughter.

333
00:18:35,386 --> 00:18:37,513
And it flies and it flies away! [laughing]

334
00:18:43,311 --> 00:18:44,687
Is school hard?

335
00:18:45,355 --> 00:18:46,648
Want some ice cream?

336
00:18:46,731 --> 00:18:48,191
No, thanks. I'm good.

337
00:18:56,616 --> 00:18:57,617
Honey.

338
00:18:59,452 --> 00:19:00,828
I've realized,

339
00:19:01,454 --> 00:19:03,373
from my own personal experience,

340
00:19:04,374 --> 00:19:06,417
that life is about

341
00:19:06,501 --> 00:19:10,755
having to carry a lot of worry
and a lot of weight on your shoulders

342
00:19:11,923 --> 00:19:14,092
That's just how it is.

343
00:19:15,176 --> 00:19:16,678
So whatever happens…

344
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:19,055
don't worry too much.

345
00:19:20,974 --> 00:19:22,642
[tender music plays]

346
00:19:22,725 --> 00:19:24,644
[chuckles, sniffles]

347
00:19:25,895 --> 00:19:28,439
I'm not sure what you're worried about.

348
00:19:29,273 --> 00:19:32,402
But it probably feels like the worst thing
that could happen to you in life.

349
00:19:32,986 --> 00:19:34,696
Well, that's understandable.

350
00:19:34,779 --> 00:19:36,823
-When I was your age…
-[sniffles]

351
00:19:36,906 --> 00:19:40,159
my whole world fell apart every single day

352
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,830
But looking back,
the things that made me cry…

353
00:19:44,455 --> 00:19:47,792
and all the things that made me weep
were really…

354
00:19:48,543 --> 00:19:51,087
Not a big deal at all?

355
00:19:51,713 --> 00:19:53,131
No.

356
00:19:53,214 --> 00:19:55,925
I'd be lying if I said
they weren't a big deal.

357
00:19:56,843 --> 00:19:59,220
If I look back
and think of all the struggles,

358
00:19:59,846 --> 00:20:01,973
uh, every single one of them

359
00:20:02,598 --> 00:20:05,893
kind of stuck to me like armor,
piece-by-piece.

360
00:20:06,894 --> 00:20:09,105
And, thanks to that,
I became a stronger person.

361
00:20:10,815 --> 00:20:11,816
So, Eui-ju,

362
00:20:12,859 --> 00:20:15,528
just don't push yourself too hard,
you know.

363
00:20:16,612 --> 00:20:19,574
Don't try to do too much.
And if it gets tough…

364
00:20:20,241 --> 00:20:22,368
Well, you can always take a break.

365
00:20:23,327 --> 00:20:25,496
I'll be right there cheering for you
on the side.

366
00:20:25,997 --> 00:20:27,248
I'll be waiting.

367
00:20:27,331 --> 00:20:30,793
Ready to bring you a nice cold
glass of water when you need it.

368
00:20:31,294 --> 00:20:32,545
[chuckles, sniffles]

369
00:20:35,381 --> 00:20:36,799
It might be tough right now.

370
00:20:37,592 --> 00:20:39,093
But everything will turn out well.

371
00:20:40,011 --> 00:20:41,012
You'll see.

372
00:20:41,763 --> 00:20:44,140
I guarantee it. Really.

373
00:20:48,311 --> 00:20:49,604
[inhales, sighs]

374
00:20:50,897 --> 00:20:52,023
Well, Dad…

375
00:20:53,608 --> 00:20:54,609
Actually…

376
00:20:55,401 --> 00:20:57,570
I do have something to tell you.

377
00:21:02,617 --> 00:21:03,785
CHAPTER 45:
HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

378
00:21:03,868 --> 00:21:05,453
[Mom] What do you think it is?

379
00:21:05,536 --> 00:21:07,580
[whispers] I don't know.
Let's wait and see.

380
00:21:22,345 --> 00:21:23,930
What? What are you doing?

381
00:21:24,555 --> 00:21:25,807
What is this?

382
00:21:25,890 --> 00:21:27,892
Eui-ju, you're gonna hurt your knees.
Come on.

383
00:21:27,975 --> 00:21:29,310
-Stand up.
-[breathing shakily] Mom, Dad.

384
00:21:29,393 --> 00:21:30,770
I write novels online.

385
00:21:33,439 --> 00:21:34,440
Novels?

386
00:21:36,526 --> 00:21:37,902
I've done it since the…

387
00:21:39,028 --> 00:21:40,029
eighth grade.

388
00:21:43,324 --> 00:21:44,659
No one read my novels.

389
00:21:44,742 --> 00:21:46,119
[sighs]

390
00:21:46,202 --> 00:21:47,578
But I found it fun.

391
00:21:50,248 --> 00:21:51,541
It was fun to

392
00:21:51,624 --> 00:21:56,129
write novels and see the characters
speak and act however I created them.

393
00:21:57,213 --> 00:22:00,049
So then I just kept writing.

394
00:22:01,092 --> 00:22:04,011
I hated waking up in the morning
and going to school.

395
00:22:04,095 --> 00:22:07,014
But I got excited at the thought of
writing novels at night.

396
00:22:07,932 --> 00:22:08,933
I…

397
00:22:10,852 --> 00:22:13,563
I know I'm not particularly good
at anything.

398
00:22:14,981 --> 00:22:16,732
For someone who wasn't good at anything,

399
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:19,152
I wasn't interested in anything.

400
00:22:20,069 --> 00:22:21,654
But for the first time,

401
00:22:23,322 --> 00:22:24,991
I found something I liked.

402
00:22:26,868 --> 00:22:27,869
And that…

403
00:22:29,495 --> 00:22:30,830
is writing novels.

404
00:22:33,332 --> 00:22:35,793
Writing novels of all things.

405
00:22:35,877 --> 00:22:38,004
[hopeful music plays]

406
00:22:38,087 --> 00:22:39,630
Like someone I know.

407
00:22:41,382 --> 00:22:42,675
-But…
-[sighs]

408
00:22:43,176 --> 00:22:44,385
…what's wrong with that?

409
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:47,847
The last novel that I wrote

410
00:22:47,930 --> 00:22:50,349
became this really huge hit.

411
00:22:50,433 --> 00:22:52,935
And got so many views and likes.

412
00:22:53,019 --> 00:22:56,480
A famous publisher offered
an immediate launch too.

413
00:22:57,064 --> 00:22:58,482
That's amazing.

414
00:22:58,566 --> 00:23:00,610
I'm so proud of you, Eui-ju.
Great job, sweetheart.

415
00:23:00,693 --> 00:23:02,111
But the thing is…

416
00:23:04,071 --> 00:23:07,450
that it's about my teachers.

417
00:23:12,830 --> 00:23:14,081
I wrote this novel

418
00:23:15,541 --> 00:23:19,045
with my teachers as,
as the main characters.

419
00:23:20,421 --> 00:23:22,506
The school found out about it and…

420
00:23:24,884 --> 00:23:27,261
the principal is holding
a disciplinary committee.

421
00:23:27,345 --> 00:23:28,346
What?

422
00:23:29,222 --> 00:23:31,057
This is the novel.

423
00:23:31,807 --> 00:23:34,060
I'm sorry. Read it after I go inside.

424
00:23:36,229 --> 00:23:37,688
[music continues]

425
00:23:37,772 --> 00:23:39,774
[door opens, closes]

426
00:23:42,443 --> 00:23:45,446
A disciplinary committee
because of writing a novel?

427
00:23:46,447 --> 00:23:48,115
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

428
00:24:01,754 --> 00:24:07,176
WE WERE FRIENDS
HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

429
00:24:11,597 --> 00:24:15,059
[Eui-ju] Hello, guys. This is Imuk.

430
00:24:16,227 --> 00:24:21,691
Today there is something I would like to
share with everyone out there.

431
00:24:22,775 --> 00:24:26,320
It is about a novel I wrote called
We Were Friends.

432
00:24:26,404 --> 00:24:28,864
The story is based on
real people around me.

433
00:24:28,948 --> 00:24:30,741
And I took parts of their everyday lives.

434
00:24:31,867 --> 00:24:34,578
the way they speak,
the way they move, their habits,

435
00:24:34,662 --> 00:24:38,374
and interpreted and adapted them
as I saw fit to create the story.

436
00:24:38,457 --> 00:24:42,461
But as a writer, I should have been able
to create something on my own,

437
00:24:42,545 --> 00:24:44,130
but I failed to do so.

438
00:24:44,213 --> 00:24:45,798
I sincerely apologize.

439
00:24:45,881 --> 00:24:49,760
I've only now realized that my writing
may have caused discomfort

440
00:24:50,720 --> 00:24:53,931
and hurt to others. I am truly sorry

441
00:24:57,226 --> 00:25:00,646
I was really happy
when I was writing this novel.

442
00:25:00,730 --> 00:25:03,065
-It gave me butterflies.
-["Why This Night?" playing]

443
00:25:03,149 --> 00:25:07,069
But that happiness was built
on something borrowed.

444
00:25:07,153 --> 00:25:09,030
No, it was actually something taken.

445
00:25:09,113 --> 00:25:10,364
without permission from someone else.

446
00:25:10,448 --> 00:25:11,282
[sniffles]

447
00:25:11,365 --> 00:25:13,951
WE WERE FRIENDS

448
00:25:14,035 --> 00:25:19,165
I'm deleting the entire novel,
to take responsibility for my actions

449
00:25:19,248 --> 00:25:21,625
If I ever get another chance to write,

450
00:25:22,585 --> 00:25:23,919
I will make sure

451
00:25:24,003 --> 00:25:26,922
I write a story based on my own struggles,

452
00:25:27,006 --> 00:25:29,383
thoughts and my imagination.

453
00:25:32,094 --> 00:25:33,679
Thank you for your support.

454
00:25:35,139 --> 00:25:36,349
And reading my novel.

455
00:25:36,432 --> 00:25:39,101
HELLO, THIS IS IMUK

456
00:25:42,605 --> 00:25:44,106
I thought

457
00:25:44,815 --> 00:25:45,816
that nothing,

458
00:25:46,609 --> 00:25:48,444
that nothing could ever stop me.

459
00:25:48,527 --> 00:25:50,029
Not the hateful comments.

460
00:25:50,112 --> 00:25:51,113
[sniffles]

461
00:25:51,197 --> 00:25:54,033
The indifference or my own flaws.

462
00:25:55,326 --> 00:25:56,827
None of it mattered.

463
00:25:57,953 --> 00:26:01,332
I believed I could keep writing anytime.

464
00:26:01,415 --> 00:26:02,958
No matter what.

465
00:26:05,503 --> 00:26:06,921
But now I can

466
00:26:08,631 --> 00:26:09,632
no longer…

467
00:26:09,715 --> 00:26:12,051
DO YOU WANT TO
DELETE THIS NOVEL?

468
00:26:15,012 --> 00:26:16,847
…be the same as before.

469
00:26:16,931 --> 00:26:23,938
"WE WERE FRIENDS" HAS BEEN
DELETED - RETURN TO MY TITLES

470
00:26:24,021 --> 00:26:27,233
["Why This Night?" continues]

471
00:26:27,316 --> 00:26:29,568
[Young-hee] I've asked you to
gather here today regarding,

472
00:26:29,652 --> 00:26:32,154
Yeo Eui-ju and her novel
about her teachers

473
00:26:32,238 --> 00:26:34,782
[Mom] Your dad and I won't
take your side unconditionally.

474
00:26:34,865 --> 00:26:38,702
I believe Eui-ju must learn a lesson from
this if she intends to keep writing.

475
00:26:38,786 --> 00:26:41,163
-[vice-principal] She must be expelled!
-I told her to keep writing.

476
00:26:41,247 --> 00:26:42,540
It's my responsibility.

477
00:26:42,623 --> 00:26:45,376
Your homeroom teacher won't be coming
to school for the time being.

478
00:26:45,459 --> 00:26:46,919
[Eui-ju] How bad is his condition?

479
00:26:47,002 --> 00:26:48,921
[Dong-ju] He probably didn't tell anyone
in case they worried.

480
00:26:49,004 --> 00:26:51,757
[Eui-ju] Mr. Ga,
why would you do something like that?

481
00:26:52,716 --> 00:26:53,801
[Woo-su] To me, you're…

482
00:26:56,053 --> 00:26:57,054
You are…

483
00:27:54,695 --> 00:27:55,696
[song ends]
